{"id":14881493,"mediaExerciseId":"1b3c38eb-3c86-400a-9b0f-f78fb2f94a52","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"15","chapterTitle":"Raising Capital","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"15.4","sectionTitle":"Underwriters","pageNumber":505,"solutions":[{"id":6009869,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to define underwriters. and green shoe provision. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/6da9fd1ead5fe2f94861c83f39fb6d91/a703c07774bbd3059f5fef4bfbd978fe/lateximg_large.png","width":1005},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/6da9fd1ead5fe2f94861c83f39fb6d91/a703c07774bbd3059f5fef4bfbd978fe/lateximg.png","width":502}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"## 15.4a\n**Underwriters** are financial intermediaries that serve a company to sell shares in an initial public offering (IPO) and potential investors. This financial specialist works directly with the issuing authority to establish the first offering share price, bought from the issuer and sold to investors through the underwriter's network.\n\n**The underwriter assists the firm in preparing for the offering, taking into account the amount of financing required, the kind of instruments to be offered, and the underwriter's agreement with the firm.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## 15.4b\n\n**Green Shoe provision** is a contractual clause that allows the underwriter to acquire additional securities from the issuing company at the listing price if they are available. \n\nThe Securities and Exchange Commission allows just one form of price stability measure. Since the underwriter may increase availability and level out price volatility, a greenshoe option gives an additional amount of market stability to a security risk. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"9200c728-f195-4db6-a569-c3da443dd6ce","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881494,"exerciseName":"1","page":508,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d48ea8af-b77e-4569-a700-7568509927ce","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-exercises-1-d48ea8af-b77e-4569-a700-7568509927ce"},{"id":14881495,"exerciseName":"2","page":508,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d5608170-87a8-4e41-b888-76a6de22682a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-exercises-2-d5608170-87a8-4e41-b888-76a6de22682a"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881492,"exerciseName":"3","page":502,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d7df1b57-10ad-4ece-a6ff-b9f4a85c6114","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-exercises-3-d7df1b57-10ad-4ece-a6ff-b9f4a85c6114"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanatio